originalText.text: I have known Dr. Shadoud for 20+ years and would highly recommend him.  Not only does he have excellent technical skills, but also a caring personality.  When I first saw him I was extremely anxious about having any dental work done, and was prone to panic attacks at the doctor.  His calm demeanor and clear expertise made me feel confident that I chose the right person to help me get the care I needed.  I have since moved to Texas, unfortunately, he is no longer my dentist - but he would be if I still lived in New York.

originalText.text: I have relied on Dr. Shadouds gentle services for more than a decade. He is never hurried or pushing a procedure to make a buck! Rare in this town. Highly recommend him and he makes for charming company as well which can lighten the prospects of a visit to the dentist.

originalText.text: Dr. Shadoud is very experienced and was great at explaining the specific needs and treatment plan. He is super patient with kids. He's very kind, and personable. I couldn't ask for a better dentist!

originalText.text: I have known Dr. Suhail Shadoud since 2013, and I saw him many times. He is a gentleman and treats you like a friend. He did fillings and crowns for me. And until now, not even a single problem with any of them. He did a crown and he was very honest about it. He said that it may not last more than a year or two because the tooth needed a surgery, but to save you a surgery, let’s do a crown for now and see.  I made that choice, and the crown lasted until now. I still see him and he still says that no need to change it for now... He always explains everything and he takes it step by step. Dr. Shadoud is very honest, reasonable, very soft handed. I very highly recommend him.
